<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-971] java module can&apos;t be compiled without ivy and network connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-971</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;eloy@zygzak:~/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java$ ant -Dnoivy=&lt;br/&gt;
Buildfile: /home/eloy/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java/build.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;init:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ivy-init-dirs:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ivy-download:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ivy-probe-antlib:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ivy-init-antlib:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;resolve:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;compile:&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;javac&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;br/&gt;
/home/eloy/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java/build.xml:125: warning: &lt;br/&gt;
&apos;includeantruntime&apos; was not set, defaulting to build.sysclasspath=last; &lt;br/&gt;
set to false for repeatable builds&lt;br/&gt;
     &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;javac&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Compiling 74 source files to &lt;br/&gt;
/home/eloy/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java/build&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BUILD FAILED&lt;br/&gt;
/home/eloy/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java/build.xml:125: Reference &lt;br/&gt;
ivy.compile.classpath not found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total time: 0 seconds&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;eloy@zygzak:~/src/c/thrift/thrift-0.5.0/lib/java$ emacs build.xml&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;path id=&quot;compile.classpath&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;path refid=&quot;ivy.compile.classpath&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/path&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It used to be (for example in 0.3.0):&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;path id=&quot;compile.classpath&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;fileset dir=&quot;${ivy.lib.dir}&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
       &amp;lt;include name=&quot;*&lt;b&gt;/&lt;/b&gt;.jar&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
     &amp;lt;/fileset&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/path&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
